🔑 ANOTHA ONE 🔑

Just closed on our first out-of-state investment in beautiful Tucson, AZ & I am still completely shooketh!! After running numbers on home after home in Boise, the math just wasn’t mathing. (SO to @kingandedge_realestate for being the most patient realtors on the planet). 

It was clear to me that it was time for a new strategy.

Am I nervous to be getting into the short term rental game, in a recession, that I’m going to manage remotely? Hell yes!! 

But! If there’s one thing I’ve learned in the past 8 years of being an entrepreneur, it’s this: 

Betting on myself is the smartest thing I’ve ever done. 

I’ll be sharing all the details about: 

☀️ why I chose this market 
📊 The tools I used for analysis 
🛋 ALL THE DECOR 
🚪My process for setting up remotely 
💎 General investing tomfoolery 

Over on the the new page, @thetucsonhavens so - follow along if you’re into that sort of thing! 🤩

.

#realestateinvesting #tucsonarizona #shorttermrentals #investorjourney #vacationrentalhomes #newairbnb #arizonaadventures #airbnbhost #investinginrealestate

Tools I used to find our latest property! ⬇️ 

1. @airdna.co - The GOAT of short term rental data! 
2. Zillow - despite having good data, ALWAYS run your own analysis on similar properties to the one your considering.🤓
3. @biggerpockets podcast (all of them). Hosts are in the game & regular talk about the best new markets to invest in + why! 
4. Mashvisor - similar to Airdna but uses a nifty heat map! 🔥
5. Network - Talk to everyone you can about what you’re looking for & if anyone you know has a contact in a market you’re considering. 

•

Posting these days feels weird (anyone else?) but, loving seeing everyone’s end-of-year highlights & thought I’d reflect back on my own. 

I’m at the point in pregnancy where it’s been 84 years & all I can remember about 2023. Yet, somehow, we managed some amazing trips to Tucson, Sundance, & San Francisco.

We enjoyed all that Boise has to offer with the people we love, many times over. We read countless books & got really good at making play doh worms. 2 year olds are so. damn. cute. 

I got more organized than I’ve ever been managing my properties. I launched an Airbnb between pregnancies, trying to cling to my old self for a moment before surrendering to babyhood once again. 

2023 was all about savoring the little moments between the chaos, & I have a feeling we’ll take that same vibe right into 2024. 

Bring on the new year & the new baby! 🐣

#happynewyear
